cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning dynamics models for real-world robots and demonstrates the approach on a quadrotor testbed. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Bayesian optimization in an active learning framework to learn the dynamics model. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper focuses on designing a controller for a given task by learning the dynamics model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to achieve better control performance. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any use of computer vision or pattern recognition techniques.
